                      W E A P O N S  E X P L A I N E D

   Weaponary: From the panels in order (Left to right)...

      EXPLOSIVE SHOT-GUN
    Once selected, your Beastie will carry a gun. Angle it with the Up/Down
    cursor keys/Joystick movements.

    Hold <SPACE BAR> or FIRE until the Power Panel builds up accordingly.
    Depress the Fire method to shoot the explosive cannon weapon. Explosive
    damage is rated as Medium.

    Energy deduction: 20%

      DYNAMITE
    Once selected, your Beastie carries a stick of explosive TNT. Press
    <SPACE BAR> or Joystick FIRE to lay it. Once done, you have the time it
    takes for the spark to go down the string before it explodes. In this
    time, just RUN to get out of there! The dynamite will fall if it's
    dropped off a ledge. Explosive damage it rated as MASSIVE!

    Energy deduction: 40%

      CLUB
    Your Beastie will carry a club once selected. You can swing this as many
    times as you wish until you actually hit something. Hitting the other
    player will cause him/her to go flying. Hitting anything else will cause
    very little damage. You do get infinite of these though!

    Energy deduction: 15%

      CLOCK-WORK MOUSE
    Top weapon I think! Once select, press SPACE BAR or FIRE to drop it and
    it will move across land (and bumpy land) until either you press
    FIRE/SPACE again to explode it on your request or if it hits a lump it
    cannot go over.

    Energy deduction: 30%

      LAZER
    Once selected, press FIRE/SPACE again to shoot it. This is a horizontal
    travelling weapon. Any thing it hits, will cause minor explosions. Once
    it reaches its length limits, it will commit ONE FINAL, BIG explosion.
    Good for making holes in hills.

    Energy deduction: 35%

      COME 'ERE!
    Once selected, Beastie carries a mechanical arm. Remember Mortal Kombat?
    Well, this is a clone of the "Scorpion" charactor.

    Pressing FIRE/SPACE will cause a string to be released. It GOES THROUGH
    TERRAIN! If it touches the other player, it will pull him/her in - even
    through terrain! An uppercut is the result of this weapon.

    Energy deduction: 25%

      DIRT BALLS
    The weapon, once selected will ACT AND WORK exactly like the Explosive
    Shot Gun. The only difference is, instead of a bullet that explodes, it
    builds a ball of dirt on terrain.

    It can be used to trap the other player, or protection for yourself.

    Energy deduction: N/A

    Next Option: More Options - bring up another panel...

      BRIDGES
    Once selected, control with your mouse or joystick where to place the
    bridge. Use the Right Mouse button to Angle it, or Left mouse button to
    place it.

    Cancel this weapon by pulling it down to the panel. This can be used for
    protection purposes or to help your Beastie cross ditches. If you're
    feeling really evil, you can trap the other player with it!

    Energy deduction: N/A

      BLOW-TORCH
    This will torch horizontally in the direction, carving a cave infront of
    you. Stop at any time by pressing FIRE/SPACE once again - after
    activated.

    Energy deduction: N/A

      DRILL
    Like the Blow-Torch, but drills directly down. Stop at any time again by
    pressing FIRE/SPACE.

    Energy deduction: N/A

      SUPER-JUMPS
    Once selected, press FIRE/SPACE to do a double-height jump. Helpful to
    get over hills, trees, etc.

    Energy deduction: N/A

      SKIP A GO
    Surprisingly, you skip a turn!

      READ BEASTIES II GUIDE FILE
    Brings up this very file that you are reading! 

      QUIT
    Quits back to the main menu

   That is infact it!


