                    H A R D  D I S K  I N S T A L L A B L E
                    ---------------------------------------

Yes indeedy, this game can easily be installed onto your Hard Disk. I have
not written a program to do this for you, mainly because I don't see the
point.

Hard Disk users must know a bit about the CLI/Workbench or they wouldn't be
able to use the damn thing, which means they must also know how to copy
files.  And my dearest, that is all you have to do to install this game onto
your bubbly, luving Hard Disk.

I will let you know the files this game needs to run though...

BeastiesII (Program - executable)

Beasties_Data/
Data1.Bin
Data2.Bin
Data7.Bin (If it exists - depending on your copy: ie. Not essential)
Data8.Bin

Libs:
Diskfont.Library

Fonts:
Courier/11
Courier.Font
Colossal/8
Colossal.font

That is it! Don't forget though, the Docs (.Guide file) should also be
included.


